---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Wingspan Egg Limit Rules: How Many Eggs Can a Bird Hold?"
  description="The egg capacity rules that trip up beginners and veterans alike."
  game="wingspan"
  gameTitle="Wingspan"
  category="Rules"
  product="wingspan-food-tokens"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    You're laying eggs in Wingspan and you notice a bird already has eggs on it
    equal to its egg limit. Can you stack more? What if you have no room
    anywhere?
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="Each bird has an egg limit printed on its card. You cannot place more eggs on a bird than its limit — but you choose which birds receive eggs." />

  <h2>How Egg Limits Work</h2>

  <div class="my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="text-2xl mb-2">🥚</div>
      <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark mb-1">The Egg Limit Number</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Printed on the bird card (usually 1–6). This is the maximum eggs that bird can hold at any time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="text-2xl mb-2">🎯</div>
      <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-bark mb-1 text-sm">You Choose Placement</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">When you lay eggs, you pick which birds get them. Spread them out or stack on one bird — your call (up to the limit).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="rule">
    When laying eggs, if all your birds are at their egg limit, you simply can't lay more. You don't lose the eggs — you just can't place them.
  </InfoBox>

  <h2>Why Egg Limits Matter Strategically</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="text-lg">📊</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">End-of-Round Goals</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Several round goals count eggs in specific habitats. High egg-limit birds in the right habitat = easy points.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="text-lg">🏆</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Each Egg = 1 Point</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">At game end, every egg on every bird is worth 1 VP. Birds with high egg limits are point multipliers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="text-lg">💰</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Eggs as Currency</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Playing a bird costs eggs (based on its column position). High egg-limit birds are also your egg bank for future plays.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The Star-Nest Power">
    Some birds have a "star nest" that can hold any type of egg. These birds are especially flexible — look for them when drafting.
  </InfoBox>

  <h2>Egg Limit Edge Cases</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Can I lay eggs if all birds are full?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1">You still take the lay eggs action (it might trigger brown powers), but you can't physically place eggs beyond the limits.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Do eggs carry over between rounds?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1">Yes — eggs stay on birds for the entire game. They're only removed when spent to play new birds.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Article>
